HAND, FOOT AND MOUTH DISEASE UPDATE (09): EUROPE (DUBLIN, IRELAND ex MALLORCA, SPAIN)
*************************************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Mon 8 Oct 2018
Source: Dublin Live [edited]
https://www.dublinlive.ie/news/dublin-news/dublin-toddler-covered-horrific-blisters-15251261


An Irish toddler was covered in horrific sores and blisters after allegedly contracting hand, foot, and mouth disease at a holiday resort in Mallorca, Spain.

Two-year-old RLC was treated in Dublin's Tallaght Hospital after her family had to cut short their holiday when she fell ill.

Around 50 people have caught the virus so far, most of them being children, at the Club Mac Hotel in Alcudia since 11 Sep 2018, the Irish Sun reports.

The Dublin toddler arrived at the hotel on 25 Sep 2018 with her mother, brother, and grandmother. Her father later flew out to Spain to be with his daughter. He said: "They borrowed a cot from the hotel for her, and we think that's how she got sick." The family noticed the sores when they went down at the beach.

Dr Sarah Jarvis, GP, said that it was absolutely possible that the disease had spread to other parts of the island. Dr. Jarvis said: "Kids can stay infectious for several weeks, so if they've been to the beach, they can spread it to other kids."

Club Mac confirmed that 48 people had been infected but said that the virus was under control. They said: "Currently, we have 2230 people staying, of which 667 are children, and only 5 cases of children with hand, foot and mouth. Please note, it is an airborne virus like the common cold and its spread has nothing to do with the cleanliness of the hotel."

[Byline: Aakanksha Surve]

