ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[Enterovirus 71 (EV-71) is a virus of the genus _Enterovirus_ in the Picornaviridae family. HFMD is usually mild, with few complications, but the EV-71 HFMD strain can be fatal because of its severe complications, which include neurological, respiratory, and cardiovascular problems. It is also more infectious than the Coxsackie virus, the most common cause of HFMD.

Although this is a report of HFMD in Europe, countries in the Asia-Pacific region have experienced increased HFMD activity, and this paper (KY Lee. Enterovirus 71 infection and neurological complications. Korean J Pediatr. 2016 Oct; 59(10): 395-401) contains useful information on EV-71 [Available at: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC5099286/.]:

[Conclusion]
--------------
"Epidemics of EV71 infection have caused many fatalities from serious neurological complications in the Asia-Pacific region since 1997 and have become a serious public health problem in these areas. Among the diverse neurological complications of EV71 infection, brainstem encephalitis is the most critical neurological manifestation, because it can cause pulmonary hemorrhage leading to death. During EV71 epidemics, the neurological complications of EV71 infection always should be considered in the differential diagnosis in children with neurological diseases. Early diagnosis and treatment with intravenous immunoglobulin and milrinone can reduce mortality and morbidity in patients with CNS involvement relating to EV71 infection. Recently, phase III clinical trials of 3 new EV71 vaccines were completed in China. However, it seems to take time for the promotion and approval of these vaccines to take effect in various countries." - Mod.LK

